  "text": "In MEB disease, the pathogenic events closely parallel those seen in FCMD. POMGnT1 is a glycosyltransferase responsible for the 2nd step in the biosynthesis of mammalian O-mannosyl glycans ( Fig. 7) . A loss of function mutation of this critical enzyme leads to a dramatic loss of glycosylation on muscle a-dystroglycan with reduced laminin a2 binding [CITATION_1] . MEB disease can be diagnosed using an enzyme assay for POMGnT1 activity to show loss of function (or reduced function) in cultured fibroblasts or lymphoblasts [CITATION_2] . The downstream manifestations include abnormal neuronal migration and skeletal muscle degeneration.",
